azelnuts, skins removed","25 g extra virgin olive oil","20 g lemon juice (approx. ½ lemon)"]},{"title":"Root vegetables","content":["700 g water","300 g raw beetroot (approx. 3), scrubbed clean and cut into eighths lengthways","400 g Dutch carrots, scrubbed clean and cut into halves lengthways","250 g purple carrots, scrubbed clean and cut into quarters lengthways","200 g parsnips, scrubbed clean and cut into quarters lengthways","200 g turnip, scrubbed clean and cut into eighths lengthways","40 g avocado oil","¼ tsp sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r90563","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-MGeMTxKtQUA\/XZWZdxAdx9I\/AAAAAAAAeNY\/bLJGU5sZ538QRBxodcMWEm7_LhubL1uUwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_c0-qhGxZY-KqaM_V.png","title":"Root vegetables with hazelnut pangrattato","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.5 g","fat":"12.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"24 g","calories":"1015 kJ \/ 242 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), sealable container, large bowl, serving platter, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Use pangrattato sprinkled over turkey and other roasted meats.","Pangrattato can be premade and frozen for up to 3 months. Simply defrost in a hot oven for a few minutes before using.","For flavour purposes, sourdough is best used in this recipe; however any type of bread can be used.","Substitute the avocado oil and salt in this recipe with any of the flavoured oils or salts from the homemade gift section."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","8 portions"]}